3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper uses standard IEEE power networks as an example to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed approach, which can be related to networking and internet architecture. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper does not explicitly mention machine learning, but the proposed mechanism can be seen as a form of optimization or learning to find the minimal number of additional actuators. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper does not focus on data structures and algorithms, but the proposed mechanism can be seen as an algorithmic approach to solve the problem of finding the minimal number of additional actuators.
